The paper deals with a machine learning problem of identifying a condition and a linear rule that can accurately model a portion of the distribution. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithms proposed in the paper involve efficient computation and optimization, which can be categorized under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of sparse regression, which is a popular technique in statistical inference (cs.SI).
